#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:2
msgid "block - temporarily block delivery of events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr "概要"

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:7
msgid ""
"block [(--local | --global)]\n"
"block --erase"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:13
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:15
msgid ""
"``block`` delays delivery of all events triggered by ``fish`` or the :doc:"
"`emit <emit>`, thus delaying the execution of any function registered ``--on-"
"event``, ``--on-process-exit``, ``--on-job-exit``, ``--on-variable`` and ``--"
"on-signal`` until after the block is removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:17
msgid ""
"Event blocks should not be confused with code blocks, which are created with "
"``begin``, ``if``, ``while`` or ``for``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:19
msgid ""
"Without options, ``block`` sets up a block that is released automatically at "
"the end of the current function scope."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:21
msgid "The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:23
msgid "**-l** or **--local**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:24
msgid ""
"Release the block automatically at the end of the current innermost code "
"block scope."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:26
msgid "**-g** or **--global**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:27
msgid "Never automatically release the lock."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:29
msgid "**-e** or **--erase**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:30
msgid "Release global block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:32
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:33
msgid "Display help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:36
msgid "Example"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:39
msgid ""
"# Create a function that listens for events\n"
"function --on-event foo foo; echo 'foo fired'; end\n"
"\n"
"# Block the delivery of events\n"
"block -g\n"
"\n"
"emit foo\n"
"# No output will be produced\n"
"\n"
"block -e\n"
"# 'foo fired' will now be printed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:52
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/block.rst:54
msgid ""
"Events are only received from the current fish process as there is no way to "
"send events from one fish process to another."
msgstr ""
